title: The X Factor Australia 2015: James Blunt takes aim at Dannii Minogue
text:
YOU COULD cut the tension with a knife on The X Factor judging panel last night.
James Blunt took aim at Dannii Minogue from the start of the show, criticising her song choices for her contestants and suggesting she’s not genuine.
“If that’s a genuine response from Dannii, that’s a real surprise from me,” Blunt told the audience after Minogue said she “didn’t like” his contestant, Louise’s, take on Nancy Sinatra’s Bang Bang.

“If it’s genuine … which I’m unsure it was …”

It is just one opinion, I preferred last weeks.”
Earlier in the show, Blunt, Guy Sebastian and Chris Isaak questioned Minogue’s choice of song for 15-year-old Georgia Denton. She sang the Jackson 5s I’ll Be There.
Judges James Blunt, Guy Sebastian, Dannii Minogue and Chris Isaak. “I think the song choice is a bit pedestrian. I know you (looking at Dannii) don’t take criticism well, but that’s what we all think,” Blunt said.
“Last time I said this you (Dannii) bit my head off, you know I think she’s really good, give her a chance.”
Sebastian chimed in: “I have to say I’m baffled so far with your journey in the live shows, I don’t understand the song choices. So far to me it’s either been too low or too screechy up here. It just saddens me, that’s all.”
X Factor: Who do you most want to save this week? Isaak was also confused by the choice of song for Denton.
“I think it’s great to see you performing better and better every week, but I don’t think this song was my favourite for you — I don’t think it suited your voice well,” he said.
The tension between Minogue and Blunt spilt on to social media with the hash tag ding ding trending online.
Tonight, two contestants will be eliminated from the competition, a first for the Australian franchise. Eight contestants will perform next week.
